<subSubSection id="C339652BFF9EF815FF13FBB9DED993B0" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9C36A0FF9EF815FF13FBB9DED993B0" blockId="27.[151,1436,1051,1257]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">
This species has previously been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FD4CFBB9DC49936C" box="[712,785,1051,1077]" name="Ghana" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ghana</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FCA7FBB9DCC1936C" author="Joly, C." box="[803,921,1051,1077]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref17099" refString="Joly, C. (2001) Contribution to the knowledge of Cetoniinae of Ghana (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Cetoniinae). Lambillonea, CI, 1 - 10." type="book chapter" year="2001">Joly 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FC2CFBB9DBDD936C" author="Mudge, A. D. &amp; Orozco, J. &amp; Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, P." box="[936,1157,1051,1077]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="113 - 174" refId="ref17706" refString="Mudge, A. D., Orozco, J., Philips, T. K. &amp; Antoine, P. (2012) The cetoniine fauna of the Upper Guinean forests and savannas of Ghana (Coleoptera: Scarabaeidae: Cetoniinae). Terrestrial Arthropod Reviews, 5, 113 - 174. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187498312 X 635319" type="journal article" year="2012">
Mudge 
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FB86FBB9DB66936C" box="[1026,1086,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). However, after further study, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FF60FB9DDE3F9300" author="Joly, C." box="[228,359,1087,1113]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" pagination="28 - 89" refId="ref17157" refString="Joly, C. (2018) Deuxieme Contribution a la connaissance des Cetoniidae du Ghana, Sous - familles des Cetoniinae et des Trichinae (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Lambillionea, 118 (1), 28 - 89." type="journal article" year="2018">Joly (2018)</bibRefCitation>
listed this species as 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FDEDFB9DDCB19300" authority="(Kolbe, 1892)" baseAuthorityName="Kolbe" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[617,1001,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraatzi">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FDEDFB9DDC669300" box="[617,830,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Niphobleta kraatzi</emphasis>
(Kolbe, 1892)
</taxonomicName>
in place of 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FBFFFB9DDA4D9301" baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1147,1301,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamipes">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FBFFFB9DDA4D9301" box="[1147,1301,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">N. squamipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(confirmed by P. Antoine and C. Joly, personal communication, 
<date id="FF9D1060FF9EF815FD78FBC1DCCC9324" box="[764,916,1123,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" value="2018-08">August 2018</date>
). Hence, we do not include 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FB64FBC1DA229325" baseAuthorityName="Gerstaecker" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1248,1402,1123,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="squamipes">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FB64FBC1DA229325" box="[1248,1402,1123,1148]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">N. squamipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as part of Ghana’s fauna until this record can be verified. Five or six species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FB81FB25DBD993F8" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1880" box="[1029,1153,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FB81FB25DBD993F8" box="[1029,1153,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Niphobleta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently recognized including three from 
<collectingCountry id="F3347630FF9EF815FE07FB09DE88939C" box="[387,464,1195,1221]" name="Ghana" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">Ghana</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FE5FFB09DDA6939C" authority="Kraatz, 1880" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1880" box="[475,766,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dominula">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FE5FFB09DD3D939C" box="[475,613,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">N. dominula</emphasis>
Kraatz, 1880
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FC8DFB09DB4A939C" authority=", Kolbe, 1892" authorityName="Kolbe" authorityYear="1892" box="[777,1042,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraatzi">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FC8DFB09DC2F939C" box="[777,887,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">N. kraatzi</emphasis>
, Kolbe, 1892
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C234D23FF9EF815FBCFFB09DE2593B0" authority="(Kraatz, 1880) (Beinhundner 2017)" authorityName="Beinhundner" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Kraatz" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Niphobleta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="niveosparsa">
<emphasis id="B957EAB2FF9EF815FBCFFB09DBAA939D" box="[1099,1266,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="178">N. niveosparsa</emphasis>
(Kraatz, 1880) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB24B51FF9EF815FF1BFB6DDE2D93B0" author="Beinhundner, G." box="[159,373,1231,1257]" pageId="27" pageNumber="178" refId="ref16250" refString="Beinhundner, G. (2017) The Cetoniinae of Africa. Privately published, Euerbach, 1174 + XXIV pp." type="book" year="2017">Beinhundner 2017</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
